In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims March 2015 as Irish-American Heritage Month. He highlights the contributions and influence of the Irish people on American culture and history. The Irish immigrants who came to America in search of a better life played a significant role in shaping the country. The Irish-American community has made valuable contributions to various sectors and continues to enrich the nation. The president emphasizes the shared values and strong bond between Ireland and the United States. He encourages Americans to celebrate Irish-American Heritage Month through appropriate ceremonies, activities, and programs.